cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.CR 

This paper primarily deals with the creation of prediction models using unstructured text data, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The use of a genetic programming algorithm and bag-of-words/phrases datasets suggests that machine learning techniques were employed, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with the analysis of data obtained from the Veterans Health Administration, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
